HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 436
By Capley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Sayler Christopher
Skelton, 2025 Top Ten Senior at Wayne County
High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Sayler Christopher Skelton is one such exceptional student, who was
recently named a Top Ten Senior of the 2025 graduating class at Wayne County High School;
and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Mr. Skelton has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in his remarkable high school career, Sayler Skelton has earned an
exemplary grade point average of 97.795 while participating in numerous extracurricular
activities, including the Beta and Math clubs, and serving as a member of the Wildcat football
and basketball teams; and
WHEREAS, his display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well for his
future success as a student at the University of Tennessee at Martin, where he hopes to obtain
a degree in physical therapy; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Skelton's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for
his parents, Chris and Andrea Skelton, his school, and his community; and
